  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI've had a report that a user is unable to make calls from a Chrome browser to the VC API (whilst the BN API works).\r\n\r\nWe can prove/disprove this bug by:\r\n\r\n1. Starting a VC API `lighthouse vc --http --http-allow-origin \"*\"`\r\n1. Getting Chrome to call `GET lighthouse/version`.\r\n\r\nChrome should report that a \"pre-flight check\" has failed.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n- I have not tried to replicate this.\r\n- I would have expected the BN and VC to exhibit identical behaviour in this regard.\r\n- I understand the the pre-flight check involves a HTTP `OPTION` call. I'm not sure how `warp` deals with this.",
