    "body": "@realbigsean thanks for taking a look. I was the one who was having issues.\r\n\r\nThe problem I'm having is making the request via JS - using fetch. I can ping the endpoint OK by hitting the URL, but an actual JS request from 127.0.0.1 is failing with:\r\n\r\n`Access to fetch at 'http://127.0.0.1:5062/lighthouse/version' from origin 'http://localhost:3000' has been blocked by CORS policy: Response to preflight request doesn't pass access control check: It does not have HTTP ok status.`\r\n\r\nTo replicate, drop this piece of code in to any JS project running on a local server:\r\n```javascript\r\nfetch(  \r\n\t'http://127.0.0.1:5062/lighthouse/validators',   \r\n\t{   \r\n\t\tmethod: 'GET',   \r\n\t\theaders: {  \r\n\t\t\t'Authorization': 'Basic api-token-YOUR_API_KEY',  \r\n\t\t\t'Content-Type': 'application/json',  \r\n\t\t}  \r\n\t}  \r\n)  \r\n\t.then(response => response.json())  \r\n\t.then(({data}) => {  \r\n\t\tconsole.log('passed', data)  \r\n\t})  \r\n\t.catch(e => {  \r\n\t\tconsole.log('failed', e.message)  \r\n\t})  \r\n```\r\n\r\nNote: using the BN api works fine via js, but I'm not having to pass the auth header to the BN endpoint, therefore not triggering CORS",
